    <!-- FOUR SEATS -->
    <section class="section section-wide">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="num">03 /</span>THE FOUR SEATS THEY ERASE
      </div>
      <h2 class="section-title">
        Four Republicans, four redraws, <span class="red">one outcome.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="section-deck">
        Each of these districts is currently competitive or Republican-held.
        Each one becomes Democratic under the proposed map. This is how you get
        to 10-1.
      </p>

      <div class="flips">
        <div class="flip">
          <div class="flip-district">DISTRICT 1</div>
          <div class="flip-rep">Rob Wittman</div>
          <div class="flip-region">NORTHERN NECK / FREDERICKSBURG</div>
          <div class="flip-change">
            <span class="was">SAFE R</span>
            <span class="arrow">→</span>
            <span class="is">LIKELY D</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flip-note">
            Redrawn to absorb Democratic-leaning Richmond suburbs and exurbs.
            Wittman's base in the rural coastal counties gets outvoted by the
            new NoVa-adjacent precincts added to the district.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flip">
          <div class="flip-district">DISTRICT 2</div>
          <div class="flip-rep">Jen Kiggans</div>
          <div class="flip-region">VIRGINIA BEACH / HAMPTON ROADS</div>
          <div class="flip-change">
            <span class="was">TOSSUP (R)</span>
            <span class="arrow">→</span>
            <span class="is">LEAN D</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flip-note">
            The state's premier swing seat gets tilted left by pulling in more
            Norfolk precincts. Kiggans — a Navy veteran nurse — goes from 50/50
            territory to a district Biden would've carried by 6+.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flip">
          <div class="flip-district">DISTRICT 5</div>
          <div class="flip-rep">John McGuire</div>
          <div class="flip-region">CENTRAL VA / SOUTHSIDE</div>
          <div class="flip-change">
            <span class="was">SAFE R</span>
            <span class="arrow">→</span>
            <span class="is">LIKELY D</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flip-note">
            Anchor pulled north to include Charlottesville and Albemarle County.
            The district stops being about Danville and Pittsylvania and starts
            being about UVA. That's the whole trick.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flip">
          <div class="flip-district">DISTRICT 6</div>
          <div class="flip-rep">Ben Cline</div>
          <div class="flip-region">SHENANDOAH VALLEY</div>
          <div class="flip-change">
            <span class="was">SAFE R</span>
            <span class="arrow">→</span>
            <span class="is">LEAN D</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flip-note">
            Dismembered. The new VA-6 would run Radford → Roanoke → Lynchburg →
            Charlottesville → Staunton → Harrisonburg — a shape that exists for
            one reason: to stretch into enough blue precincts to flip. Cline
            might have to run in VA-9 instead.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
