    <!-- DARK MONEY / FOLLOW THE MONEY -->
    <section class="section section-wide">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="num">04 /</span>FOLLOW THE MONEY
      </div>
      <h2 class="section-title">
        The YES campaign isn't a Virginia movement.<br />
        It's a <span class="red">Washington wire transfer.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="section-deck">
        If this amendment were good for Virginians, Virginians would be paying
        for it. They're not. Per <strong>Virginia Public Access Project</strong>
        filings, more than <strong>90%</strong> of large contributions to the main
        YES committee — <em>Virginians for Fair Elections</em> — come from out-of-state
        Democratic-aligned dark-money groups. Two donors alone account for over <strong
          >$40 million</strong
        >.
      </p>

      <div class="funding-wrap">
        <div class="funding-bar-wrap">
          <div class="funding-bar-label-row">
